<seg id="1045">"Povray; supports two methods of super-sampling. as a standard is an adaptive, non-recursive method; adaptive because the super-sampling uses the adjacent pixels. the second method is adaptive-recursive; recursively because each pixel will be split up again and again because the rector depth depends on the calculated color values."</seg>
<seg id="1046">"if you choose the first method, POV-Ray tracks a beam per pixel. if the difference between the color values exceeds the defined threshold, then both pixels are calculated by tracking a certain additional number of pixels with super-sampling. if you set the depth value to 4, a grid of 5 x5 (25) will calculate additional beams per pixel."</seg>
<seg id="1047">"the difference between two pixels is calculated as follows: r 1, g 1 and b 1 are the values for red, green and blue of the first pixel, r 2, g 2 and b 2 are the values for red, green and blue of the second pixel."</seg>
